window.bookSummaryJSON = "❖<b> QUEEN OF MONSTERS<i> </i></b>❖<br><br>I sling whiskey like it’s penance and smile like I don’t feel the weight of the world.<br>Brooklyn’s my kingdom — bruised, bitter, and crawling with shadows.<br>I keep my head down.<br>My walls up.<br>My secrets buried.<br>Until <b>he</b> walks in.<br>Storm-gray eyes.<br>Blood on his knuckles.<br>A man who doesn’t blink when violence erupts —<br>he <i>breathes</i> it.<br><br>They call him <b>Rhett Costa</b>.<br>Some say he’s mafia muscle.<br>Others say he’s already dead inside.<br>But he watches me like I’m more than a bartender in a dive bar.<br>Like I’m a secret he’s been waiting to claim.<br><br>And the night two armed strangers try to rob my bar,<br>he steps out of the shadows like a man possessed.<br>Not for justice.<br>Not for duty.<br><b>For me.</b><br>Now, I’m on their radar —<br>men with names that make bodies disappear and empires fall.<br>Rhett. Milano. Enoch.<br>They say they’re protecting me.<br>But I know better.<br><b>Because monsters don’t save you. They claim you.</b><br>And if I’m not careful,<br>I won’t just lose my freedom—<br><br><b>I’ll lose myself to the three men who were sent to erase me…<br>but might just burn the world to keep me.</b>"; 
